<topic id="preferences-editor-print">
  <title>Print Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Configure the Application<indexterm>Editor
              preferences<indexterm>print</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To configure the <uicontrol>Print</uicontrol> options, <ph
        conkeyref="reusable.menus/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="editor author developer">Print</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140820T142638-0400" comment="Print preferences do not seem to exist at all in Eclipse. If they are in there, where are they hiding?"?>
      <uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Edit
      modes/Pages</uicontrol>.<?oxy_comment_end?>
    </p>
    <p product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">This page allows you to customize the
      headers and footers added to a printed page when you print from the <xref keyref="mode.text"
          ><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol></xref> mode or <xref keyref="mode.author"
          ><uicontrol>Author</uicontrol></xref> mode editors. These settings do not apply to the
        <xref keyref="mode.grid"><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref> and schema
        <?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140827T134416-0400" comment="Need to add a link here once there is a topic to link to."?><uicontrol>Design</uicontrol><?oxy_comment_end?>
      modes.</p>
    <p product="developer developerEclipse">This page allows you to customize the headers and
      footers added to a printed page when you print from the <xref keyref="mode.text"
          ><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol></xref> mode editor. These settings do not apply to the <xref
        keyref="mode.grid"><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref> and schema
        <?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140827T134416-0400" comment="Need to add a link here once there is a topic to link to."?><uicontrol>Design</uicontrol><?oxy_comment_end?>
      modes.</p>
    <p>You can specify what is printed on the <uicontrol>Left</uicontrol>,
        <uicontrol>Middle</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Right</uicontrol> of the header and footer
      using plain text of any if the following variables: 
    </p>
           <ul>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140827T135057-0400" comment="This may be a case where it is better to conref out of another topic rather than moving all the editor variables to a reusables file. Mybe that is true generally of reference topics? The alternative is to link to the reference rather than conrefing it. "?>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-currentFileURL"
              ><?oxy_comment_end?></li>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-cfne"/>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar_cp"/>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar_tp"/>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-env"/>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-system"/>
            <li conref="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-date"/>
          </ul>         
    <p>For example, to show the current page number and the total number of pages in the top right
      corner of the page, write the following pattern in the <uicontrol>Right</uicontrol> text area
      of the <uicontrol>Header</uicontrol> section: <codeph>${cp} of ${tp}</codeph>. </p>
    <p>You can also set the <uicontrol>Color</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Font</uicontrol> used in the
      header and footer. Default font is <codeph>SansSerif</codeph>.</p>
    <p>You can place a line below the header or above the footer by selecting
        <uicontrol>Underline/Overline</uicontrol>.</p>
  </body>
